            "description": "Sirara is a mountain range in the Levant that is to be identified with Mount Hermon (biblical ḥermôn; modern Gebal aš-Šaiḫ; amorite śᵉnir), as well as the southern part of Anti-Lebanon mountains (modern Gebal aš-Šarqīf). Sirara is mentioned in Assyrian royal inscriptions composed in the reigns of Sennacherib. Esarhaddon, and Ashurbanipal.",
